{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b56021e0-b5bb-4d2e-a43c-fee99e35ecc2","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a standard .NET MAUI `ContentPage` property — that's likely why it has no effect. Here's what you need for true edge-to-edge:\n\n### iOS — Disable Safe Area Insets\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n```\n\n### Android — Edge-to-Edge\n\n.NET 10 targeting Android 15+ is edge-to-edge by default. For older API levels, in your `MainActivity.cs` or platform startup:\n\n```csharp\n#if ANDROID\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\n// In your MainActivity or window setup:\nWindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n#endif\n```\n\n### Hide the Navigation Bar\n\nIf you're inside a `Shell` or `NavigationPage`, hide the nav bar:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Shell -->\n<ContentPage Shell.NavBarIsVisible=\"False\" Shell.TabBarIsVisible=\"False\" ...>\n\n<!-- Or NavigationPage -->\n<ContentPage NavigationPage.HasNavigationBar=\"False\" ...>\n```\n\n### Image Setup\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage Padding=\"0\" ...>\n    <Image Source=\"photo.jpg\"\n           Aspect=\"AspectFill\"\n           HorizontalOptions=\"Fill\"\n           VerticalOptions=\"Fill\" />\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Summary of likely culprits:**\n1. `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` is a no-op — use `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"`\n2. Nav/tab bar still visible — hide with Shell or NavigationPage properties\n3. Missing `Padding=\"0\"` on the page\n4. `Aspect` not set to `AspectFill`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d84ac36d-5f5e-4612-90aa-bcd79190997a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is working on a .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10 and wants an image to go edge-to-edge (behind status bar and navigation bar). They've tried `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but still see padding.\n\nThis is a common MAUI question. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. In .NET MAUI, `SafeAreaEdges` is an iOS-specific concept. Setting it to `None` on iOS should allow content to go behind the safe area insets.\n\n2. But there are several other things that could cause the image not to fill edge-to-edge:\n   - If the page is wrapped in a `NavigationPage` or `Shell`, the navigation bar consumes space and needs to be hidden using `NavigationPage.HasNavigationBar=\"False\"` or `Shell.NavBarIsVisible=\"False\"`.\n   - On Android, edge-to-edge rendering requires explicit configuration. Starting with Android 15, apps are edge-to-edge by default, but MAUI might need the window configured to extend behind system bars.\n   - Shell's tab bar also needs to be hidden if present.\n   - The `Image` control should use `AspectFill` for its `Aspect` property to cover the full area.\n   - ContentPage might have default padding or margins that need clearing.\n\nFor .NET 10 MAUI, I'm thinking through the platform-specific approaches. On iOS, I need to handle the safe area—either with `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` or through `SafeAreaEdges`, though I'm not entirely certain which approach is current for this version. I need to clarify the actual APIs available in .NET MAUI. On iOS, I can use the platform-specific configuration to disable safe area handling with `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` in XAML or the C# equivalent. For Android, edge-to-edge rendering requires handling window insets, which has improved in newer versions. I'm also considering how navigation bar hiding fits into this approach. For iOS I need to use the `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` platform-specific property, while Android 15+ handles edge-to-edge rendering by default in .NET 10, though older versions might require calling the appropriate WindowCompat method. The main gotchas are usually the navigation bar still showing up and default page padding eating into the edges, so I should make sure to hide the nav bar and set all padding to zero.\n\nOne more thing—if the image isn't filling the space properly, I need to set the `Aspect` property to `AspectFill` so it scales correctly without letterboxing.","outputTokens":1798,"requestId":"F3D1:13D2B1:1E9F95A:228609F:69E81C6D"},"id":"0fb30952-196f-49eb-9324-c7247e8176ae","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:55:42.383Z","parentId":"76b20ebe-22d5-4dad-bcd8-073bf79a8147"}
